Having compiled the [ClientReceipt.sol](https://gist.github.com/abrkn/0cf2b89ab48969ec62eb) contract, I submit to my own private network (eth-go version from develop branch today):

```
sendTransaction:
[
  {
    "from": "003deb0170f7b942b5848e2934f5410c9531f12e",
    "gas": "0xf4240",
    "value": "0x1",
    "data": ""
  }
]
```

which yields

```
{
  "id": "85920b12-11b4-44e6-8ea9-69206f57028c",
  "jsonrpc": "2.0",
  "result": "0xdd3e150a127f367d93ef5e996e0ede8e61da6a34"
}
```

Link to [contract description json](https://gist.github.com/abrkn/1189c402a2c3cf9350bd)

I call the contract:

```
ClientReceipt = eth.contract([{"constant":fa...[],"name":"BoxClosed","type":"event"}]);
contract = ClientReceipt('0xdd3e150a127f367d93ef5e996e0ede8e61da6a34');
contract.sendTransaction({
    from: eth.coinbase,
    value: '0x100'
}).deposit(0xdeadbeef);
```

Now, the call should have create a log entry? Deposit is `indexed`.

However,

```
{
  "jsonrpc":"2.0",
  "id": 1,
  "method": "eth_getLogs",
  "params": [
    {
        "fromBlock": "0x0",
        "address": "0xdd3e150a127f367d93ef5e996e0ede8e61da6a34"
    }
  ]
}
```

Results in

```
{
    "id": 1,
    "jsonrpc": "2.0",
    "result": []
}
```

ref #629. Also had no luck with creating and polling filters.
